  "body": "http://doc.servo.org/servo/index.html is the rustdoc documentation for Servo\u2019s own crates, those of all dependencies (submodules), and Rust\u2019s (for the version used by Servo, which is usually a few weeks behind Rust master.)\n\nCurrently, this is a total of 69 crates that are listed in alphabetical order. Instead, I would like the sidebar to have three sub-sections (Servo, submodules, and Rust) each listing the corresponding crates. The sidebar is generated by a copy of [`src/librustdoc/html/static/main.js`](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/8a02304a44/src/librustdoc/html/static/main.js#L682-L698), and therefore is not easy to customize.\n\nCould rustdoc help with this? Perhaps, rather than adding a feature for exactly what Servo wants, enable arbitrary behavior by providing a hook for overriding the bit of JS that generates the sidebar?\n",
